<paragraph blockId="14.[151,710,295,355]" box="[151,511,331,355]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">
<figureCitation box="[151,278,331,355]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1599,1623]" captionTargetBox="[250,1337,181,1575]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[250,1337,181,1575]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dorsal view of the whole specimens that represent the analyzed species. A, Chaetopleura lurida, BL 27.48 x 15.70 mm, Majahua, Acapulco (CNMO 5229). B, Chaetopleura hanselmani, BL 11.02 x 7.16 mm, Tlacopanocha, Acapulco (CNMO 5804). Ischnochiton muscarius, C, BL 16.62 x 9.77 mm, Angosta, Acapulco (CNMO 5202); D, BL 15.12 x 9.55 mm, Barra de Potosí Protegida, Petatlán (CNMO 5338); E, BL 18.30 x 10.17 mm, Troncones, La Unión (CNMO 5327); F, BL 14.98 x 9.51 mm, La Barrita, Petatlán (CNMO 5315). G, Callistochiton elenensis, BL 12.32 x 7.76 mm, La Barrita, Petatlán (CNMO 5823). H, Callistoplax retusa, BL 20.41 x 9.68 mm, Parque de la Reina, Acapulco (CNMO 5185). Stenoplax limaciformis, I, BL 17.56 x 7.21 mm, Parque de la Reina, Acapulco (CNMO 5179); J, BL 20.12 x 9.15 mm, Tlacopanocha, Acapulco (CNMO 5208); K, BL 17.65 x 8.29 mm, Las Gatas, Zihuatanejo de Azueta (CNMO 5254); L, BL 19.78 x 9.84 mm, Isla Grande, Zihuatanejo de Azueta (UAGRO 0024). Chiton albolineatus, M, BL 23.84 x 14.63 mm, Piedra de Tlacoyunque, Tecpan de Galeana (CNMO 5337). Tonicia forbesii, BL 33.41 x 17.86 mm, Isla Grande, Zihuatanejo de Azueta (CNMO 5255). Acanthochitona arragonites, O, BL 8.80 x 5.2 mm, Las Salinas, Copala (CNMO 5267). Lepidochitona salvadorensis, P, BL 10.63 x 5.7 mm, Barra de Potosi Protegida, Zihuatanejo de Azueta (CNMO 5332)." pageId="14" pageNumber="465">Figures 2G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[290,351,331,355]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[151,1436,181,1843]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ischnochiton muscarius, SEM images of a specimen BL 13.1 mm; valves in dorsal view, A, head valve; B, intermediate valve IV and in ventral view, C, detail or articulamentum of valve IV; D, tail valve in dorsal view. E, aesthete system detail of intermediate valve IV; F, girdle scales; G, detail of girdle scales surface; H, radular teeth; I, detail of major lateral teeth. Callistochiton elenensis, disarticulated valves of a specimen BL 11.09 mm, Manzanillo, Acapulco (CNMO 5304); dorsal view of valves, J, head valve; K, intermediate valve IV." pageId="14" pageNumber="465">6J–K</figureCitation>
