<figureCitation box="[362,433,331,355]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[151,1436,181,1843]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. Callistochiton elenensis, disarticulated valves of a specimen BL 10.9 mm, Manzanillo, Acapulco (CNMO 5304); A, dorsal view of tail valve. Valves in ventral view, B, head valve; C, intermediate valve IV; D, tail valve. SEM images of a specimen BL 9.97 mm, valves in dorsal view; E, head valve; F, intermediate valve IV; G, tail valve, and H, ventral view of intermediate valve IV; I, detail of girdle scales; I, radular teeth; J, K, detail of central teeth." pageId="14" pageNumber="465">7A–K</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[445,511,331,355]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-18@17.[151,1436,181,1866]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Callistochiton elenensis, SEM images of a specimen BL 11.6 mm, Manzanillo, Acapulco; A, B radular teeth. Callistoplax retusa, disarticulated valves of a specimen BL 17.74 mm; valves in dorsal view, C, head valve; D, intermediate valve IV; E, tail valve. Valves in ventral view shows the articulamentum details; F, head valve; G, intermediate valve IV; H, tail valve. SEM images of a specimen BL 15.1 mm; valves in dorsal view; I, head valve; J, intermediate valve IV; K, tail valve." pageId="14" pageNumber="465">8A–B</figureCitation>
